ZCZC GE78
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 082300 UTC
DURING MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 991 WILL LIE
W OF IRELAND WITH CYCLONIC CONDITIONS ACROSS MOST SEA AREAS. ANOTHER DISCRETE
LOW PRESSURE CENTRE WILL FORM NEAR THE SHETLAND ISLES THEN MOV NWARDS LATER
TUESDAY. A SECONDARY LOW WILL RUN INTO FITZROY DURING TUESDAY EVENING. HIGH
PRESSURE WILL LIE NEAR ICELAND AND DEVELOP LATER OVER THE N SEA. A SIMILAR
PRESSURE PATTERN WILL PERSIST THROUGH WEDNESDAY WITH COMPLEX LOW DEVELOPING
OVER THE BRITISH ISLES AND SLWY FLN. THIS LOW WILL MOV SWARDS THROUGH THURSDAY
WITH RIDGE CONDITIONS FM THE ICELANDIC HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING OVER NERN
BRITAIN. STRG WINDS DURING MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY MORNING PERHAPS WITH
OCCASIONAL GALES IN FAIR ISLE WILL MOD LATER. WINDS MAY CONTINUE OCNL STRG
IN FAIR ISLE ON WEDNESDAY THEN STRG N WINDS WILL SPREAD TO ACROSS OTHER
NERN SEA AREAS THROUGH THURSDAY
